{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4ee36303-9478-456a-85f9-f04ba2fcaf5a","content":"The migration is straightforward. In your project file, simply **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Why this is enough:** Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4+, `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` is the **default** runner. Setting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` was explicitly opting out of it. Removing that property (or setting it to `false`) switches you to the new platform automatically — no additional packages needed.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **CLI** | Use `dotnet test` as before, but some VSTest switches (e.g. `--logger`) change to `--report-*` style flags |\n| **Filters** | `--filter` still works, but the syntax is now `--filter \"Name=MyTest\"` |\n| **`.runsettings`** | Still supported via `--settings` |\n| **CI/TRX output** | Add `<OutputType>trx</OutputType>` or pass `--report-trx` if you need TRX reports |\n\nRun `dotnet test` after the change to verify everything works.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2a13a0ef-5e80-4d03-9218-4b3e58413260","outputTokens":367,"requestId":"0433:3FE43:1F85424:2353BA9:69E81A52"},"id":"76a7f09f-f452-4c5c-a6ae-0925bf24e36a","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:20.044Z","parentId":"159468a1-58bd-45ba-ae89-cc4d64f571e1"}
